individual_results.question: Explain the concept of overfitting in machine learning.
individual_results.expected_answer: Overfitting occurs when a machine learning model learns the training data too well, including its noise and outliers, resulting in poor performance on new, unseen data.
individual_results.predicted_answer: Overfitting in machine learning occurs when a model is too complex and captures noise or outliers in the training data, leading to poor performance on new, unseen data. It is characterized by high accuracy on the training data but low accuracy on test data, as the model fails to generalize well. This happens when the model's complexity exceeds that of the underlying relationship in the data.

individual_results.question: Explain the concept of regularization in machine learning.
individual_results.expected_answer: Regularization is a technique used to prevent overfitting by adding a penalty term to the loss function, encouraging simpler models with smaller parameter values.
individual_results.predicted_answer: Regularization in machine learning is a technique used to prevent overfitting by adding a penalty term to the loss function, which encourages simpler models with smaller parameter values. Common types include L1 regularization (Lasso), which adds the sum of absolute values of parameters; L2 regularization (Ridge), which adds the sum of squared parameters; and Elastic net, which combines both L1 and L2 methods. Dropout is another form of regularization specifically for neural networks that randomly sets some neurons to zero during training.
